      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BUSINESS IN HEAVEN (2) had enough speed to lead from a wider barrier last start and while he couldn't keep it going there he was good when placed at this circuit and distance prior. Race fit now and gets his lowest draw of the campaign so far. This looks his chance to return to the winners' list. RAVISHING SLOY (10) had been building to a win and it arrived last week when he raced wide from a similar draw to this and fought well to score by 2 metres at this circuit and distance. He could deliver again. VITE MONET (8) is on the radar after decent efforts from this barrier in his last two outings here including a close second two back. UNFAZED NZ (9) raced wide but stuck on for second last week. With better fortune he could go one better.",
